						<div class="postbody">This is pretty cool! You may find <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7579" class="postlink">this thread</a> of interest for background collisions. I recently struggled with this myself. For your game you won't have gravity, and your velocities may be constant, but the sequence of steps needed for correct background collision and response is there.
<br />
<br />Also I admire someone that can come up with a good, unique idea for a game and implement it without a mapper. Every time I sit down to design a game I end up with something that reads "remake [name of awesome commercial game] but make it WAY cooler!" Not very practical or feasible <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />
<br />
<br />Good luck!</div>

